<catalogue library="false" id="a0ff-9897-0c6f-8acd" name="Ascentic Way" gameSystemId="sys-61df-4102-3143-2eae" gameSystemRevision="2" revision="1" battleScribeVersion="2.03" type="catalogue" xmlns="http://www.battlescribe.net/schema/catalogueSchema">
  <selectionEntries>
    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Army Rule: Acts of Faith" hidden="false" id="8a37-9731-583d-1b69" sortIndex="1">
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink targetId="629c-c441-50b1-a5c9" id="3871-ab1b-278d-4172" primary="true" name="Configuration"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <rules>
        <rule name="Acts of Faith" id="a7b7-5a29-3395-c968" hidden="true">
          <comment>Army rule With lore</comment>
          <description>*&quot;Through jubilation, Swiftness. Through discipline, destruction. Through piety, Victory&quot; - Scroll of the Ascentic Warpath, line 288*

Units with the Acts of Faith special rule gain the Act of Faith (0 AP) complex action. It works like so

Act of Faith (0 AP): Select one of the units acts of faith that is has not used this battle. The unit takes a morale test if the morale test is passed, that unit gains the associated benefit of the act of faith. If it is failed, then the unit gains no benefit. Under either circumstance, the unit may not use that Act of Faith for the rest of the battle.</description>
          <modifiers>
            <modifier type="set" value="false" field="hidden">
              <conditions>
                <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
              </conditions>
            </modifier>
          </modifiers>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Acts of Faith" id="7c9f-49a5-0e8d-f767" hidden="false">
          <comment>Army rule Without lore</comment>
          <description>Units with the Acts of Faith special rule gain the Act of Faith (0 AP) complex action. It works like so

Act of Faith (0 AP): Select one of the units acts of faith that is has not used this battle. The unit takes a morale test if the morale test is passed, that unit gains the associated benefit of the act of faith. If it is failed, then the unit gains no benefit. Under either circumstance, the unit may not use that Act of Faith for the rest of the battle.</description>
          <modifiers>
            <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
              <conditions>
                <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
              </conditions>
            </modifier>
          </modifiers>
        </rule>
      </rules>
    </selectionEntry>
    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Army Rule: Zealous" hidden="false" id="cdf5-97fc-01a2-e313" sortIndex="2">
      <rules>
        <rule name="Zealous" id="77ce-e4fa-d28b-6131" hidden="true">
          <comment>Army rule With lore</comment>
          <description>*&quot;Through faith, strength. Through conviction, loyalty. Through meditation, peace.&quot; - Scroll of the Ascentic Warpath, line 293*

When a unit with the Zealous X special rule makes a morale test during their activation, they may instead choose to automatically pass that moral test, However, at the end of that units activation, that unit takes X unavoidable damage.</description>
          <modifiers>
            <modifier type="set" value="false" field="hidden">
              <conditions>
                <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
              </conditions>
            </modifier>
          </modifiers>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Zealous" id="1cf4-9886-29ed-60b5" hidden="false">
          <comment>Army rule Without lore</comment>
          <description>When a unit with the Zealous X special rule makes a morale test during their activation, they may instead choose to automatically pass that moral test, However, at the end of that units activation, that unit takes X unavoidable damage.</description>
          <modifiers>
            <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
              <conditions>
                <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
              </conditions>
            </modifier>
          </modifiers>
        </rule>
      </rules>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink targetId="629c-c441-50b1-a5c9" id="62ba-1c2c-7bd2-5b09" primary="true" name="Configuration"/>
      </categoryLinks>
    </selectionEntry>
